<p>
<strong>DIRECTIONS:</strong>
A general access area, although this one is a
Rest Area. Follow the directions for Gin Gin
Bridge Reserve, then proceed along Wambianna
Road toward Warren past the other riverside
access sites on this side of the river - see
previous entries - until you see the Rest Area
sign (see photo).
</p>
<div class="fishing-line-separator"></div>
<p>
<strong>COORDINATES:</strong>
31&#176;47'46&rdquo;S, 147&#176;58'47&rdquo;E
</p>
<div class="fishing-line-separator"></div>
<p>
<strong>ROAD ACCESS:</strong>
Good.</p>
<div class="fishing-line-separator"></div>
<p><strong>BOAT LAUNCHING:</strong> Not recommended.</p>
<div class="fishing-line-separator"></div>
<p><strong>ACCESS ALONG THE BANK:</strong> Difficult. Very steep.</p>
<div class="fishing-line-separator"></div>
<p><strong>CAMPING ALLOWED FACILITIES ON-SITE:</strong> There is a garbage bin and a turn-around loop
for caravans.</p>
<div class="fishing-line-separator"></div>
<p><strong>OTHER INFORMATION:</strong> Rest area is just past some large Fertilisers tanks
by the road.</p>
